We acknowledge Reviewer 2's request for statistical tests to interpret our simulation results. However, when interpreting simulation results such as ours, statistical tests are actually inappropriate (see White et al. 2014, ''Ecologists should not use statistical significance tests to interpret simulation model results'').

This is because, practically, statistical power in a simulation is entirely determined by replication. Philosophically, simulation models such as ours violate the assumptions underlying statistical hypothesis testing. Hence, reporting the results of statistical tests would not be informative in our model, and we do not want to risk misleading readers into thinking such results would be biologically meaningful. 

We now explain that statistical tests are not appropriate for interpreting our model results, citing White et al. (2014) explicitly (L405-L409).

